description:
Approval of details pursuant to condition 19 (nature conservation plan) of planning permission ref: P091143 dated 28 September 2009, which reads:
No development shall take place until a landscape and nature conservation plan (“the Plan”) has been submitted to and approved in writing by the local planning authority covering full details of:
i) artificial nesting/roost bricks/bird boxes to be located within the fabric of the proposed buildings or on existing trees;
ii) a biodiversity green roof/brown roof including materials;
iii) a green corridor above the railway tunnel parapet including boundary protection;
iv) a planting and boundary treatment scheme for the remainder of the greenspace;
v) the phasing of (i) to (iv) above;
vi) the ongoing management of (i) to (iv) above
The Plan shall be implemented in accordance with the phasing approved and the measures set out in (i) to (iv) above shall thereafter be maintained and managed in accordance with the Plan.
